-- Russian Budget May Pay for Gasoline Price Freeze, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-01-30T04:18:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/russian-budget-may-pay-for-gasoline-price-freeze-vedomosti-says.html
Russian  oil companies  that agreed to
freeze gasoline prices at the pump until March presidential
elections may be allowed to pay reduced export duties on fuel
oil and diesel as compensation,  Vedomosti said , citing two
unidentified state officials.  Deputy Prime Minister Igor Sechin has already tasked the
Energy Ministry, the Economy Ministry and the  Finance Ministry 
with creating the mechanism for compensation, Vedomosti said,
citing the two ministry officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 